    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, a definitive example of the widebody 996 chassis. This specimen features the M96.03 3.6L flat-six, delivering linear power delivery across the rev range via VarioCam Plus variable valve timing. The 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox offers precise gate selection, feeding a viscous-coupling all-wheel-drive system for neutral handling dynamics. The IMS bearing has been proactively upgraded with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the rear main seal remains bone dry. Suspension kinematics are factory-correct with no bushing compliance issues, while the four-piston monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors provide exceptional swept area for fade-free deceleration. This is a concours-level example with a flawless DME overrev report and pristine underbody integrity.",
      "price": 48750.0,
